General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (3) Municipal participation; and
2 (4) Observed impacts on winter road response."
3 SECTION 2. The sum of ten million dollars ($10,000,000) in recurring funds is
4 appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of Transportation for each fiscal year
5 beginning with the 2026–2027 fiscal year to support operational costs under this Article.
6 The sum of twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) in nonrecurring funds is appropriated from the
7 General Fund to the Department of Transportation for the 2026–2027 fiscal year to support the
8 acquisition and installation of snow and ice-removal equipment under this Article. Funds
9 appropriated under this section shall not revert and shall remain available for expenditure until
10 expended.
11 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the Highway Fund to the Department of
12 Transportation for the 2026-2027 fiscal year the sum of five million dollars($5,000,000) in
13 nonrecurring funds to be used by the Department to build up a salt and brine reserve to distribute
14 to local governments in need, with priority given based on need, geography, and population.
15 SECTION 4. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
